* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.025
Doc string 
function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

Doc string 
function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

Doc string 
function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

Doc string 
function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);

  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.003
Doc string 
function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

Doc string 
function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }

    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

Doc string 
function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);

  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

Doc string 
function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.002
Doc string 
function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

Doc string 
function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

Doc string 
function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);

  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

Doc string 
function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);

  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.002
Doc string 
function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

Doc string 
function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);

    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

Doc string 
function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);

  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

Doc string 
function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

Doc string 
function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}

* def roundAwayFromZero = 0.000
Doc string 
function(value, decimalPlaces) {
  
  var num = Number(value);
  if (isNaN(num)) {
    return num;  // Return as is if it's not a valid number
  }
  
  var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces);
  var valueToRound = num * factor;
  var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? 
    (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : 
    Math.round(valueToRound);
  
  return roundedValue / factor;
}
